    {
      "text": "%python\n\n# \u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\n# PARAGRAPH 4 — Utility Functions\n# \u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\n\ndef create_sequences_fast(data: pd.DataFrame,\n                           features: list,\n                           seq_len: int):\n    \"\"\"\n    Build (N, seq_len, n_features) array using numpy stride trick.\n    FIX 5: replaces Python for-loop → 10x faster, no list appends.\n    Returns: (sequences np.ndarray, scaler StandardScaler)\n    \"\"\"\n    clean \u003d data[features].dropna()\n    if len(clean) \u003c seq_len:\n        return np.empty((0, seq_len, len(features)), dtype\u003dnp.float32), None\n\n    scaler  \u003d StandardScaler()\n    scaled  \u003d scaler.fit_transform(clean.values).astype(np.float32)\n    n, nf   \u003d scaled.shape\n    n_seq   \u003d n - seq_len + 1\n\n    # Stride trick — zero-copy sliding window\n    s0, s1     \u003d scaled.strides\n    sequences  \u003d np.lib.stride_tricks.as_strided(\n        scaled,\n        shape\u003d(n_seq, seq_len, nf),\n        strides\u003d(s0, s0, s1)\n    ).copy()   # .copy() makes contiguous for Keras\n\n    return sequences, scaler\n\n\ndef build_gru_ae(seq_len: int, n_features: int, encoding_dim: int \u003d 32):\n    \"\"\"GRU Autoencoder — unchanged architecture.\"\"\"\n    model \u003d Sequential([\n        GRU(64, return_sequences\u003dTrue, input_shape\u003d(seq_len, n_features)),\n        Dropout(0.2),\n        GRU(encoding_dim, return_sequences\u003dFalse),\n        Dropout(0.2),\n        RepeatVector(seq_len),\n        GRU(encoding_dim, return_sequences\u003dTrue),\n        Dropout(0.2),\n        GRU(64, return_sequences\u003dTrue),\n        Dropout(0.2),\n        TimeDistributed(Dense(n_features)),\n    ])\n    model.compile(optimizer\u003d\u0027adam\u0027, loss\u003d\u0027mse\u0027)\n    return model\n\n\ndef reconstruction_errors(sequences: np.ndarray, model) -\u003e np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"MSE reconstruction error — single batched predict call.\"\"\"\n    recon \u003d model.predict(sequences, batch_size\u003d256, verbose\u003d0)\n    return np.mean(np.square(sequences - recon), axis\u003d(1, 2))\n\n\nprint(\"✅ P4 done — utility functions ready\")\n\n",
      "user": "anonymous",
      "dateUpdated": "2026-03-26 10:13:04.006",
